# `docs/skill-plan.md` — authoring instructions

`skill-plan.md` is the **Stage 1 planning document** — fill it at the start of building a skill, before writing any phase content. It lives at `docs/skill-plan.md` in your skill. The filled scaffold copy lives at [`skill-scaffold/docs/skill-plan.md`](../skill-scaffold/docs/skill-plan.md).

## How to fill each section

### Action checklist
Work through the checklist **top to bottom** before moving to Stage 2. Each item represents a decision or verification. Tick `- [x]` only when done. These are the gates before you start writing phase content.

### Delivery mode
Choose one:
- **`static_built`** — `build.py` assembles everything into `AGENTS.md` once. Re-run when sources change. Best for most skills.
- **`runtime_injection`** — `generate.py` assembles prompt slices on demand per phase. Use when the skill must stay up-to-date without a build step.

Record your choice and a one-line rationale. Must match `skill-config.json` → `delivery.mode`.

### Suggested stages and phases
Sketch the pipeline before creating any files. One row per phase. You don't need the final names yet — this is a planning table. Align with `content/parts/process.md` once you write it.

### Suggested rules and scanners
List the rules you expect to need. For each rule, note the scanner (or "manual check" if no scanner yet). Write "none — add in Stage 2" if you have nothing yet.

### Suggested library components
Which shared norms will the model see in every phase? List the library files you expect to create or reuse. These become entries in `skill-config.json` → `library_files`.

### Actor / role when using the skill
Who runs each phase — human, AI, or mixed? What does the skill optimise for (speed, consistency, correctness)? This shapes the role file.

### Operator, workspace, and delivery artifacts
Describe how the Operator chain works for this skill: Python compile → `build.py` → scanners. What drift does each step catch? Set `active_skill_workspace` here and confirm it matches `conf/abd-config.json`.

### Authoring checklist
This section is **populated by scaffold** from `abd-skill-builder/content/parts/library/authoring-checklist.md`. If you are filling this manually, paste the checklist body from that file (drop the `# Skill authoring checklist` title line). Use `- [ ]` / `- [x]` to track progress. The first unchecked box is where you resume after an interruption.

## File location

`docs/skill-plan.md` is a **non-runtime** file — it is never merged into `AGENTS.md` or injected into a phase bundle. Keep all runnable instruction content in `content/parts/`.
